SP.P:
Pardon me; I know very well what I am about; 
(singing and dancing)—The head
upright:— (singing and dancing) The body thrown gracefully for∣ward.

Why, you nasty, good for nothing, false-hearted creature,
you ought to be ashamed of your∣self, so you ought: I do love you, then;
I own I do; 
[Bursts out a crying] and if you had not treated
me so, I would seen him further with all his fine promises; but now I'll
go and keep my coach out of spight.
